HEADWORD: Acetimetry
<hw>Ac`e*tim"e*try</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or
method of ascertaining the strength of vinegar, or the proportion of
acetic acid contained in it.</def> <rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
